benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: POST coverage includes valid payload scenarios with minimal and extended payloads across TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC21, and TC26 to validate success, optional parameters, and backward compatibility
Edge cases are addressed with TC18 (empty pluginProperty), TC19 (extra unexpected parameters), and TC20 (large pluginProperty) to validate robustness of input handling

Validation and input checks are well covered via TC08 (invalid bundleId), TC09 (invalid requestedDate), TC10 (invalid billingPolicy), TC11 (missing required header), TC12 (missing body), as well as TC15 (SQL injection) and TC16 (XSS) for security-related input validation
Authorization and authentication scenarios are covered by TC11 (missing header) and TC13 (unauthorized access), with appropriate 400/401 responses
Error handling is comprehensively tested including 404 not found (TC06, TC07, TC22, TC23), 500 internal error (TC24), and 503 service unavailable (TC14)
Security tests include SQL injection (TC15) and XSS (TC16)
State variation tests cover empty and partially populated databases (TC22, TC23) and regression scenarios (TC25, TC26)
Performance-related tests (TC27-TC29) and resource usage (TC30) along with accessibility considerations (TC31)
gaps: Duplicate submission / idempotency scenario is not covered
403 Forbidden authorization scenario is not tested (only 401 in TC13)
Caching behavior / ETag handling is not tested
Rate limiting / throttling tests are not present
Observability/audit-logging checks are not explicitly tested
recommendations: Add a dedicated duplicate submission test to verify idempotency and how repeated requests are handled
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions beyond the 401/400 cases
Introduce tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and verify caching behavior
Add rate limiting / throttling tests to assess resilience under burst traffic
Incorporate observability checks such as auditing/logging the bundle transfer events
Add explicit post-transfer data-state verification to ensure the bundle moves from source to target as expected
